##Bullfrogs, bamboo rats, edible snakes... These game, can you eat it?

The following article comes from our remedial class, the author of the Committee on Remedial Class

Adult 100,000 Whys, rediscover your curiosity about the world

The outbreak of new crown pneumonia has once again drawn attention to the potentially deadly risks of overeating game. Today, not only people's safety awareness is constantly improving, from national to local governments are also as soon as possible to improve the management of wildlife-related laws and regulations, wildlife "fasting" is also one after another.

However, there are still many questions: how to distinguish wild animals? Are All wild animals inedible? After the end of the epidemic, bullfrogs, turtles, edible snakes... can you eat it?

Don't worry, bullfrogs and turtles are not banned

First of all, to give you "worry" for a long time, "eat goods" to eat a reassurance, you miss the bullfrog has not been banned, or can eat later.

Zhang Xianliang, director of the Bureau of Fishery and Fishery Administration of the Ministry of Agriculture and rural areas, said at a State Council joint prevention and Control Mechanism press conference on March 5 that the vast majority of turtle farming, including Chinese soft-shelled turtles and turtles, and bullfrog and American frog, two introduced species of frogs, can be raised for food.

The bullfrog, also known as the American water frog, is a large edible frog native to North America and Mexico.

Bullfrog in China's catering market has existed for a long time, is not a new species, but the real fire is only in recent years.

Meituan and the restaurant business management from the media "restaurant owners, " a joint release of the "China catering report 2018, " shows that in that year, the restaurant industry in the category of the most notable feature is the explosion of single-product catering growth, for example, bullfrog, crawfish, Sauerkraut fish as a brand more and more single-brand restaurants.

"curiosity daily" Also quoted meituan-dianping data reported that as of February 2018, the number of national bullfrog specialty restaurants exceeded 22,000, nearly three years from 2018, the National Bullfrog characteristic restaurant has a growth rate of about 10% .

In the last two years, bullfrogs have become more and more popular, challenging crayfish "Internet celebrities" status.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
From the comparison of Baidu Index, we can find that although the "sound" of Bullfrog is not as high as that of crayfish, compared with crayfish with obvious seasonal characteristics, the attention of netizens to bullfrog is relatively stable on the whole. In this way, bullfrogs can be described as a "long-term flow of water" type players.

According to Meituan's 2019 Spring Festival consumption map, souffl√©, dirty tea and charcoal hotpot are the three most searched for online food during the 2018 Spring Festival.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
But while bullfrogs and American frogs are clearly edible, the outlook for other edible frogs remains uncertain, given the varying standards of fasting in the wild.

Recently, media reports said, Taishan, Guangdong, Thailand Tiger Frog farmers, are facing the dilemma of being able to raise can not sell.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
However, aquatic wildlife and amphibians are less restricted than terrestrial wildlife because they are relatively safe and distant from humans.

Even the "no eating" clause in the "Shenzhen Special Economic Zone ban on eating wild animals" (draft draft for comments)(hereinafter referred to as the "Shenzhen Wild animals no eating order") , which is called the "most strict no eating order" , nor are there too many additional regulations on aquatic wildlife.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
In general, the rare and endangered aquatic wildlife protected by the Wildlife Protection Act is clearly inedible. In addition to whether the aquatic wildlife is edible, "Wildlife Protection Law" , Fisheries Law and other relevant laws and regulations have made provisions.

The situation of land wildlife fasting is complicated

Due to the close relationship between terrestrial wild animals and human beings, they are easy to be infected by bacteria or viruses.

In general, the animals that are often used as food in our daily life are called livestock and poultry. Except for livestock and poultry, they are wild animals.

Livestock and poultry mainly refer to human needs for meat, eggs, milk and fur, said Han Xu, deputy director of the Fisheries and Fisheries Administration Bureau of the Ministry of Agriculture and rural areas, at a news conference of the Joint Prevention and Control Mechanism of the State Council on February 27, any of various animals domesticated by long labour.

There are four main DIFFERENCES BETWEEN LIVESTOCK AND WILDLIFE:

1. Livestock and poultry are usually raised artificially for a long period of time and are widely used in production
2. The phenotypes of livestock and poultry have changed substantially compared with those of wild animals, and there are stable economic characters of artificial selection
3. Stable epidemic disease prevention and control system has been formed in livestock and poultry
4. In line with international practice

Stable epidemic disease prevention and control system has been formed in livestock and poultry

In line with international practice

Simple understandings, such as pigs, cows, and sheep, are foods that we normally think of as edible, easily purchased in our daily lives, and often consumed. And Bats, pangolins and other animals, I believe that most people do not necessarily have access to, will not easily try.

As for what is a livestock and poultry, Shenzhen's wildlife ban lists a clear range, including nine types of livestock and poultry: pigs, cattle, sheep, donkeys, rabbits, chickens, ducks, geese and pigeons.

* Legally protected wild animals are expressly forbidden to eat

Legally protected wild animals are expressly forbidden to eat

In fact, the Wildlife Protection Law of the People's Republic of China clearly stipulates that the production, management and illegal purchase for food of wildlife under state key protection are prohibited.

For example, the most familiar Pangolin, every year we can see a large number of smuggling Pangolin News.

Recently, the Customs Anti-smuggling Bureau of Nanning and Hefei, in conjunction with the Guangxi Public Security Department, has smashed a Pangolin scale smuggling criminal gang and seized 820 kilograms of smuggled pangolin scales at the scene. If not seized, the scales will eventually be sold to markets in places such as Henan for sale.

It is reported that a Pangolin body about 0.4 ~ 0.6 kilograms of scales, if this calculation means that perhaps more than 1,300 pangolins have been served as food on the table.

And that's just the tip of the iceberg. In November 2017, Shenzhen Customs seized 11.9 tons of Pangolin scales, which means that nearly 20,000 pangolins have been killed.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Behind the frequent smuggling cases, there is strong consumer demand.

In 2017, Wu Shibao, a professor at the South China Normal University, told reporters that China consumes about 300,000 pangolins a year, of which more than 95 percent come from abroad and the vast majority are illegal.

But there is so much consumer demand, just because people think that pangolins have medicinal value, Can "cure all diseases" , which is a big reason for the booming wildlife market.

Ironically, there is no clear-cut conclusion as to whether wild animals are "good" or not, but they are likely to carry deadly viruses.

Previous studies by groups such as the South China Agricultural University have suggested that pangolins may be intermediate hosts in the COVID-19. But this conclusion still lacks conclusive evidence, has not been confirmed.

And besides seeking"big fill"outside, also the person eats wild animal is to"show off"or be out of"curious"psychology.

Wild animals that can be listed for protection are rare, precious and naturally expensive. Bear paws have long been considered one of the "eight treasures" and have long been considered top-notch ingredients, so smuggling is also active.

An analysis of the smuggling situation of wild animals in China's customs in recent years found that from 2008 to 2018, there were 390 cases of illegal smuggling of wild animals and their products published on the official website of the General Administration of Customs, of these, 5.88% were related to smuggling of tiger bones, musk deer, bear bile and bear paws.

In late 2019, police in Heilongjiang cracked a rare smuggling case of large wild bear paws, seizing 214 wild brown bear paws.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

* Can The wild animals raised by factory still be eaten?

Can the wild animal of artificial breeding still eat?

In fact, in addition to the endangered and rare wild animals protected by law, there are many wild animals that are not protected by law. It does not seem illegal to sell and eat such animals, as a result, there are many people who exploit loopholes for profit.

In addition, some wild animals are allowed to be farmed, but many traders will sell the wild species of these animals directly, which caused a lot of trouble for wildlife management.

Like a meat snake. The taste of snake is a famous dish in Hunan, and the market of Meat Snake in Changsha is relatively developed.

In 2007, the Hunan Wildlife Protection Association was quoted as saying that Changsha consumes about 10,000 kilograms of snakes a day, and that at least 30 percent of these snakes are wild.

In 2013, Zhou Canying, president of the Changsha Wildlife Conservation Association, told reporters that the investigation showed that there were nearly 300 restaurants, restaurants and restaurants that operated snakes in Changsha, fewer than 120 of them have wildlife permits. If the average daily consumption in the peak season is 35 kilograms, 300 restaurants will consume 10 tons of snakes per day.

And in "eat snake big province" Guangdong, the meat snake market wants more huge. In 2008, an article pointed out that the monthly sales of meat snakes in Guangzhou could reach more than 600 tons.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Image: Delving into Shunde

After the outbreak, including meat snakes, bamboo rats, civet cats, wild pigs and other wild animals that were once allowed to be farmed can continue to be sold and eaten.

The Shenzhen Wildlife Food Ban includes both protected and non-protected terrestrial wildlife, as well as captive-bred and farmed terrestrial wildlife.

However, in the face of complex circumstances, the national level is also actively developing or improving the relevant directory, to clarify the scope of wild animals and livestock.

Liu Yongfu, director of the Office of the Leading Group for Poverty Alleviation and Development under the State Council, said at a news conference on March 12 that the relevant departments are working out a detailed list of what can not be raised and what can be raised.
